description.plain:
Coupling powerhouse vocals with simultaneously catchy and powerful songwriting, Ava Max quickly became a pop hit-maker at the start of the 2020s. Born Amanda Ava Koci on February 16, 1994, in Milwaukee, Wisconsin to Albanian immigrants, Max didn’t get her start in the music industry until 2017 with her feature on “Clap Your Hands”.

Part of a crop of massively successful pop singers from the Balkans (which also includes Dua Lipa, Bebe Rexha, and Rita Ora), Ava Max’s lyrical themes of female empowerment, electropop style, and eccentric fashion quickly drew comparisons to fellow pop star Lady Gaga. Before long, she scored her breakout hit through “Sweet but Psycho”, topping charts around the world and peaking at number ten on the Billboard Hot 100.

Max followed up the success of “Sweet but Psycho” with two more Hot 100 hits — “Kings & Queens” and “My Head & My Heart” — before releasing her debut album, Heaven & Hell. The set debuted and peaked at #27 on the Billboard 200 albums chart, going on to sell a million units and achieve Platinum certification from the RIAA.

Max scored another hit in 2022 with “The Motto”, a collaboration with Dutch DJ and producer Tiësto. Her second album, Diamonds & Dancefloors is slated for release in 2023.

To date, Ava Max has certified single sales of 12.5 million in the United States alone.

songs.full_title: Sweet but Psycho by Ava Max
songs.title: Sweet but Psycho

description.plain:
Ava Max said in an interview with JAMS 96.3,

The track is about a girl who is misunderstood in a relationship. She thinks she’s going out of her mind and psycho. But in reality, she’s just a strong, independent female. In the end, the guy loves all of her sides – sweet, psycho (as he likes to call it).

A music video for the song was released on August 27, 2018. It was directed by Bengali-American filmmaker Shomi Patwary. Ava Max said in the same interview that it takes the song to a crazy place because of her love of theatrics.

Ava Max appeared on Genius' series Verified to explain the meaning of the song.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p9NSpo-qtv0

“Sweet but Psycho” peaked at #1 in 12 countries, including the UK. After spending several weeks on the Billboard Bubbling Under Hot 100, it went up to #87 in the last week of December. It peaked at #37 as of the week ending January 19.

songs.full_title: Kings & Queens by Ava Max
songs.title: Kings & Queens

description.plain:
“Kings & Queens” is a song by Ava Max, released on March 12, 2020 as a single from her album Heaven & Hell.

The song initially went through around 10 iterations, which included different melodies and production, before the final version was completed. Ava stated that “Kings & Queens” is about how the world would be a better place if queens ruled the world and likened it to her previous song “So Am I”, acknowledging that it contained a similar message about empowerment.

songs.full_title: So Am I by Ava Max
songs.title: So Am I

description.plain:
“So Am I” is the follow-up single by Ava Max after her 2018 Platinum breakout hit, “Sweet but Psycho”.

The electro-pop song details the tale of empowerment on how Ava relates to being different and how those differences makes everyone unique.

In an interview, Ava Max said that it’s

About what makes people unique and different from each other. It’s about loving yourself, being different, being an outcast and not fitting in the format that society wants to put us in — just celebrating what really makes you different. Whenever I’m feeling down, I remind myself that my flaws make me perfect, because in reality there is no perfect."
